{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a407ef33-677c-4732-85db-e0fbbf9a887a","content":"Yes, you'll hit **framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 dropped support for older TFMs. Here's your situation:\n\n| Target | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — requires **net6.0+** |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — requires **net6.0+** |\n\nBoth `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are also **end-of-life** from Microsoft.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to replace those with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`). You can also simplify to the single `MSTest` meta-package instead of separate `TestFramework` + `TestAdapter` references.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"97324195-cab8-44ab-90f6-5359961a7bd8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nKey compatibility issues with MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's out of support from Microsoft as well). MSTest v3 supports .NET 6.0+.\n   - `.NET Core 3.1` (`netcoreapp3.1`) is no longer supported. MSTest v3 requires at least .NET 6.0 for .NET Core targets.\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) is still supported in MSTest v3, so that target should be fine.\n\nThe real compatibility issues are with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`, which both fall below the minimum .NET 6.0 requirement for MSTest v3. I should also note that MSTest v3 lets you use a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of managing separate `TestFramework` and `TestAdapter` packages, and there are some breaking changes around assertion behavior and async support in test lifecycle methods.","outputTokens":794,"requestId":"083C:E2933:8260BA8:9154A0F:69EAD524"},"id":"